translated: Ahlmann, Hugo Jacob, provincial physician in Falköping, born on August 4th, 1894 in Skallmeja, Skaraborg County, eldest son of director Leo A. and Ulrika Carolina Anna Margaretha Raab. Married in 1943 to M’ai Henriksson, and has one son named Hans, born in 1944. Ahlmann passed his final school exam in Skara in 1913, studied medicine in Uppsala and received his medical degree in Stockholm in 1923. He was made a temporary assistant physician at Måhlla sanatorium in 1921, a temporary first assistant physician at Eskilstuna hospital in 1922, then a physician at Mariestad hospital in 1923, and an assistant physician at Kålltorp hospital in Gothenburg from 1924 to 1925. From 1926 to 1927, he served as a temporary intern and assistant physician at the medical department of Gothenburg children's hospital, then as an intern from 1927 to 1928, and as a medical assistant from 1928 to 1929. He was a physician at Rävlanda children's hospital from 1929 to 1931, and a district physician and hospital physician in Bredbyn from 1931 to 1936 and in Mörbylånga from 1936 to 1947, before becoming a district physician in Falköping in 1947. Ahlmann served as a naval physician fellow in 1924, a naval physician second grade in 1926, a naval physician first grade in 1929, including as a barracks physician in Karlskrona, and a naval physician first grade in reserve from 1929.
